node.title: Ardern confirms Prince Andrew no longer holds NZ military patronage
node.content: ["The Prime Minister has confirmed Prince Andrew no longer holds a New Zealand military patronage after he was stripped off all military and royal patronages by the Queen.", "\"Buckingham Palace has recently announced that, with the Queen's approval and agreement, the Duke of York\u2019s military affiliations and Royal patronages have been returned to the Queen,\" a statement from Jacinda Ardern's office says.", "\"In New Zealand, the Duke of York was formerly the Colonel-in-Chief of the Royal New Zealand Army Logistic Regiment (The Duke of York's Own).\u00a0As a result of patronages returning to the Queen, his appointment has now ended.", "\"Any further changes to Royal patronages and appointments would be a matter for the Prime Minister to raise with the Queen of New Zealand in due course.\"", "More to come.", "\u00a0"]
